<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>Robert La Follette's Progressive Party campaign of 1924 advocated for:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Conservative economic policies</option>
            <option letter="b">Public ownership of resources and labor rights</option>
            <option letter="c">Immigration restrictions</option>
            <option letter="d">Support for big business</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>La Follette's 1924 Progressive Party campaign advocated for public ownership of water power and railroads, stronger labor rights, farm relief, and opposition to monopolies. His platform represented a challenge to conservative Republican policies and corporate power. Though he received nearly 5 million votes, his defeat highlighted the declining influence of progressivism in 1920s America.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
